sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2142007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Composite part containing ccdA and blue chromoprotein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: we used this part to make our e.coli resistant against the ccdB. The part also contains a blue chromoprotein as marker.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lukas Rieder

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: amilCP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This chromoprotein, amilCP, naturally exhibits very strong color when expressed. The color is blue/purple and is visible to naked eye, thereby requiring no instruments to observe. This DNA was provided by Jeffrey Miller at UCLA. It was made BioBrick-compatible after removal of one illegal internal restriction site (EcoRI).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Illegal internal restriction site had to be removed (EcoRI).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2142006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part allows to make e.coli resistant against the ccdB Toxin. We used constitutive promoters to be sure our E.coli is always protected from the toxin.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lukas Rieder
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It is important to express it constitutive because of the short-life
